The '''{{ill|Sōhō-chūen Kofun|ja|双方中円墳}}''' (そうほうちゅうえんふん) is a type of {{ill|Kofun|ja|古墳}} burial mound. It is characterized by a circular main mound with '''two rectangular extensions''', one on each side.

== Overview ==
Whereas '''{{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳}}''' (keyhole-shaped kofun) feature a '''single''' rectangular extension at the front of a circular main mound, the '''Sōhō-chūen Kofun''' has '''two''' such extensions, one on either side.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} These kofun are seen primarily in the early '''{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代}}'''. 

While '''Zenpō-kōen-fun''' typically have a designated '''frontal direction''', it is unclear which side was considered the "front" in '''Sōhō-chūen Kofun'''.{{Sfn|Izumimori|1991|p=55}}

As of 2015, only '''four confirmed examples''' of Sōhō-chūen Kofun are known in Japan.{{Sfn|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}} Among these, '''{{ill|Kushiyama Kofun|ja|櫛山古墳}}''' is notable for having '''one smaller extension''' compared to the other.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} 

Furthermore, during the '''{{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代}}''', certain burial mounds also exhibited '''keyhole-shaped''' or '''Sōhō-chūen-like''' structures. These early forms likely '''evolved into the standardized keyhole-shaped and Sōhō-chūen kofun''' of the Kofun period.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} 

== List of Known Sōhō-chūen Kofun ==
{{座標一覧}}
* '''{{ill|Akeai Kofun|ja|明合古墳}}''' ({{ill|Tsu, Mie|ja|津市}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県}})
* '''{{ill|Kushiyama Kofun|ja|櫛山古墳}}''' ({{ill|Tenri, Nara|ja|天理市}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県}}, {{ウィキ座標|34|33|24.68|N|135|51|7.54|E|region:JP-29_type:landmark|name=Kushiyama Kofun}})
* '''Three tombs in the {{ill|Iwaseoyama Kofun Cluster|ja|石清尾山古墳群}}''' ({{ill|Takamatsu, Kagawa|ja|高松市}}, {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県}}):
  * '''{{ill|Nekozuka Kofun|ja|猫塚古墳}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|39.63|N|134|1|25.08|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Nekozuka Kofun}}) - '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''.
  * '''{{ill|Kagamizuka Kofun|ja|鏡塚古墳}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|55.72|N|134|1|47.73|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Kagamizuka Kofun}}) - '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''.
  * '''{{ill|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun|ja|稲荷山北端1号墳}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|58.07|N|134|2|22.32|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}}) - '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''. Previously believed to be a '''Zenpō-kōen-fun (前方後円墳)''', but '''confirmed as a Sōhō-chūen Kofun in 2015'''.{{Sfn|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}}

### Related Site:
* '''{{ill|Tatezuka Burial Mound|ja|楯築墳丘墓}}''' ({{ill|Kurashiki, Okayama|ja|倉敷市}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県}}, {{ウィキ座標|34|39|47.01|N|133|49|31.76|E|region:JP-33_type:landmark|name=Tatezuka Burial Mound}})  
  - A '''Yayoi-period''' '''Sōhō-chūen-style''' '''mounded tomb (墳丘墓)'''.

