Furthermore, during the '''{{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yayoi period|qq=}}''', certain Kofuns also exhibited '''keyhole-shaped''' or '''Sōhō-chūen-like''' structures. These early forms likely '''evolved into the standardized keyhole-shaped and Sōhō-chūen kofun''' of the Kofun period.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} 

