The '''{{ill|Sōhō-chūen Kofun|ja|双方中円墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōhō-chūen Kofun|qq=}}''' (そうほうちゅうえんふん) is a type of [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] Kofun. It is characterized by a circular main mound with '''two rectangular extensions''', one on each side.

== Overview ==
Whereas '''[[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]]''' (keyhole-shaped kofun) feature a '''single''' rectangular extension at the front of a circular main mound, the '''Sōhō-chūen Kofun''' has '''two''' such extensions, one on either side.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} These kofun are seen primarily in the early '''[[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]'''. 

While '''Zenpō-kōen-fun''' typically have a designated '''frontal direction''', it is unclear which side was considered the "front" in '''Sōhō-chūen Kofun'''.{{Sfn|Izumimori|1991|p=55}}

As of 2015, only '''four confirmed examples''' of Sōhō-chūen Kofun are known in Japan.{{Sfn|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}} Among these, '''[[:en:Kushiyama Kofun|Kushiyama Kofun]]''' is notable for having '''one smaller extension''' compared to the other.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} 

Furthermore, during the '''[[:en:Yayoi period|Yayoi period]]''', certain Kofuns also exhibited '''keyhole-shaped''' or '''Sōhō-chūen-like''' structures. These early forms likely '''evolved into the standardized keyhole-shaped and Sōhō-chūen kofun''' of the Kofun period.{{Sfn|Sōhō-chūen Kofun (Sekai Daikyakka)}} 

== List of Known Sōhō-chūen Kofun ==
{{GeoGroup}}
* '''[[:en:Akeai Kofun|Akeai Kofun]]''' ([[:en:Tsu, Mie|Tsu, Mie]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]])
* '''[[:en:Kushiyama Kofun|Kushiyama Kofun]]''' ([[:en:Tenri, Nara|Tenri, Nara]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]], {{ウィキ座標|34|33|24.68|N|135|51|7.54|E|region:JP-29_type:landmark|name=Kushiyama Kofun}})
* '''Three tombs in the [[:en:Iwaseoyama Kofun Cluster|Iwaseoyama Kofun Cluster]]''' ([[:en:Takamatsu|Takamatsu, Kagawa]], [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]]):
** '''{{ill|Nekozuka Kofun|ja|猫塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nekozuka Kofun|qq=}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|39.63|N|134|1|25.08|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Nekozuka Kofun}}) * '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''.
** '''{{ill|Kagamizuka Kofun|ja|鏡塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagamizuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|55.72|N|134|1|47.73|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Kagamizuka Kofun}}) * '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''.
** '''{{ill|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun|ja|稲荷山北端1号墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}''' ({{Coord|34|19|58.07|N|134|2|22.32|E|region:JP-37_type:landmark|name=Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}}) * '''Pile-stone tomb (積石塚)'''. Previously believed to be a '''Zenpō-kōen-fun (前方後円墳)''', but '''confirmed as a Sōhō-chūen Kofun in 2015'''.{{Sfn|Inariyama Hokutan 1-gō Fun}}

=== Related Site: ===
* '''{{ill|Tatezuka Kofun|ja|楯築墳丘墓|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tatezuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 楯築遺跡|1=Tatetsuki Site|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11541408}}''' ([[:en:Kurashiki|Kurashiki, Okayama]], [[:en:Okayama Prefecture|Okayama Prefecture]], {{ウィキ座標|34|39|47.01|N|133|49|31.76|E|region:JP-33_type:landmark|name=Tatezuka Kofun}})  
** A '''Yayoi-period''' '''Sōhō-chūen-style''' '''mounded tomb (墳丘墓)'''.

